member.name: F:BZFramework.Math.RomanNumeral.SubtractionThreshold
member.summary: The subtraction threshold dictates the manimum value of the lower division before another character of the higher division, preceeded by subtractors, is added. (i.e. 1800, with SubtractionThreshold of 1, is 'MCCC'; 1800, with SubtractionThreshold of 2, is 'MCCM')
